  "instructions": [
    "Heat a large pot over medium heat and add a splash of coconut oil.",
    "Add lemongrass, galangal, and kaffir lime leaves; saut\u00e9 for 2 minutes until fragrant, then deglaze with 1 cup of fish stock, scraping up the browned bits.",
    "Pour in the remaining fish stock and bring the broth to a gentle simmer. Add snapper pieces and simmer gently for 4\u20135 minutes, until the fish turns opaque (internal temp 145\u00b0F).",
    "Stir in coconut milk, fish sauce, and lime juice; adjust seasoning if needed. Re\u2011warm gently, ensuring it does not boil.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with scallions, basil, cilantro, and sliced chili if desired."
